HEADWORD: Panshon
<hw>Pan"shon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An earthen vessel
wider at the top than at the bottom, -- used for holding milk and for
various other purposes.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Halliwell.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

